1.

Description:
Implement a Consent Evaluate API in Admin Server to determine consent status for a user.
The API will check consent in the local database, integrate with Communication Service / EIS Wrapper APIs when required, and return consent status along with Privacy Notice and Purpose details.

This API will be used at MIF Login and Merchant Panel Login touchpoints to validate whether consent is active or re-consent is required.

API Details
Endpoint: POST /admin/consent/evaluate

Request Body:
{
  "merchantMifId": "String",
  "dpCIF": "string",
  "dpMobile": "string",
  "touchPointId": "string",
  "purposeSetId": "string"
}

Response Body:
{
  "merchantMifId": "String",
  "isConsentActive": true,
  "consentStatus": "Active | Inactive | Expired | Revoked",

  "consentReadResponse": {
    "status": "String",
    "consentId": "string",
    "dpIP": "String",
    "locale": "string",
    "timestamp": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ",
    "version": "String"
  },

  "privacyNoticeResponse": {
    "version": "String",
    "privacyText": "String"
  },

  "purposeResponse": {
    "purposes": [],
    "code": "String",
    "version": "int",
    "title": "String",
    "description": "String",
    "isEssential": "String",
    "validityDays": "long",
    "timestamp": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ",
    "locale": "string"
  }
}

Developmnt Flow:-
Step 1 — Validate Request

Step 2 — Check Consent in Local DB
Case A — Consent Active
If status = Active and not expired:
Return response from local DB.
isConsentActive = true
Do NOT call Communication Service.

Step 3 — If Consent Not Active (Inactive / Expired / Revoked / Not Found)
Call Consent Read API (via Communication/EIS Service).
Case A — Communication Service returns Active Consent
Insert/Update consent in local DB.
Update consent version, timestamp, status.
Return isConsentActive = true.

Case B — Communication Service returns New Consent + Privacy + Purpose
This means re-consent required.
Then:
Save privacy notice in privacy_master table.
Save purpose in purpose_master table.
Compare privacy version & purpose version with master table:
If different → update master tables.
Return:
isConsentActive = false
privacyNoticeResponse
purposeResponse

Step 4 — If Communication/EIS Service Down
Fallback mechanism:
Read latest privacy notice from privacy_master
Read latest purposes from purpose_master
Return them in response.
isConsentActive = false.

Acceptance Criteria
API returns active consent if available locally.
If not available, system calls Consent Read API.
Privacy and Purpose master updated when version changes.
Fallback works when external service is down.
Response structure matches agreed contract.
Consent stored per Mobile + MIF ID + Touchpoint + PurposeSet.
Expiry calculated using validityDays.

