  ]
}

Kafka consumer will:
Call EIS Consent Write API
Receive consentId
Update local DB sync_status = SUCCESS / FAILED

Step 4 — Return Response
Immediately return:
{
  "message": "Consent has been updated"
}

Acceptance Criteria
API validates request.
Consent sync_status updated to PENDING.
Kafka event published.
API returns success immediately.
Consumer calls EIS API and updates DB.
Retry mechanism implemented.
Revocation updates status = Revoked.
Consent ID stored after CCMS success.


