Issue: Admin Server – Pending Consent Sync Scheduler

Description
Implement a Scheduler in Admin Server to retry syncing consents whose sync_status = PENDING.
Flow:
Scheduler fetches pending consents from DB.
Scheduler publishes each consent to Kafka (Communication Service).
Communication Service calls CCMS Consent Write API.
Communication Service publishes SUCCESS / FAILED event on Kafka.
Admin Server Kafka Consumer listens to the response event.
If SUCCESS → update DB sync_status = SUCCESS.
If FAILED → keep sync_status = PENDING (will retry via scheduler).
This ensures reliable and asynchronous consent sync with CCMS.


Complete Flow (Step-by-Step)
Step 1 — Scheduler Job
Create scheduler that runs every 5 minutes.
@Scheduled(cron = "0 */5 * * * *")
Scheduler will:

Fetch consents where sync_status = PENDING
Send them one by one to Kafka topic → consent.write.request


Step 2 — Fetch Pending Consents
SELECT * FROM consent_table
WHERE sync_status = 'PENDING'
ORDER BY updated_at ASC;

Process records one by one to avoid duplicate writes.

Step 3 — Publish to Kafka

Kafka Topic: consent.write.request

Kafka Payload:

{
  "merchantMifId": "String",
  "dpCIF": "String",
  "dpMobile": "String",
  "dpEmail": "String",
  "dpIP": "String",
  "locale": "String",
  "timestamp": "String",
  "consentAction": "String",
  "touchPointId": "String",
  "purposeSetId": "String",
  "purposes": [
    {
      "purposeCode": "String",
      "purposeVersion": "int",
      "consentAction": "capture/modify/revoke"
    }
  ]
}

After publish → Do NOT change status. Keep PENDING.

Step 4 — Communication Service
Communication Service will:
Consume Kafka event.
Call EIS Consent Write API.
Publish result event to Kafka topic:
consent.write.response


Step 5 — Admin Server Kafka Consumer
Admin server listens to: consent.write.response

Response Payload:
{
  "merchantMifId": "String",
  "dpCIF": "String",
  "dpMobile": "String",
  "consentId": "String",
  "status": "SUCCESS | FAILED",
  "errorMessage": "String",
  "timestamp": "String"
}

Step 6 — Update DB Based on Response
Response Status	DB sync_status
SUCCESS	SUCCESS
FAILED	PENDING

If SUCCESS:

Update sync_status = SUCCESS
Update consent_id
Update last_sync_time

If FAILED:

Keep sync_status = PENDING
Update error_message
Will retry via scheduler

Database Table (consent_table)

Acceptance Criteria
Scheduler runs every 5 minutes.
Fetches consents with sync_status = PENDING.
Publishes Kafka message for each consent.
Communication Service sends SUCCESS/FAILED event.
Admin Kafka consumer updates DB:
SUCCESS → SUCCESS
FAILED → Remains PENDING
System retries automatically until success.
Proper logging implemented.
